<item>
            <title>[SPARK-2490] StackOverflowError when RDD dependencies are too long</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-2490</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When performing some transformations on RDDs after many iterations, the dependencies of RDDs could be very long. It can easily cause StackOverflowError when recursively visiting these dependencies in Spark core. For example:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;var rdd = sc.makeRDD(Array(1))&lt;br/&gt;
for (i &amp;lt;- 1 to 1000) {&lt;br/&gt;
  rdd = rdd.coalesce(1).cache()&lt;br/&gt;
  rdd.collect()&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
